messages.message:
Hey team, I am trying to create a project with a sample file on https://aihub-sandbox.internal.instabase.com/. When I add a field, I keep getting the error that the extraction failed. Have we seen this error today? The logs point to this line (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/5291a8d52278575ca594a27f0ccbc5a9555bcbd9/shared-utils/py-utils/grpc-utils/src/py/instabase/utils/grpc/client.py#L61) since no error is returned.

This also showed up on my crafting env
This probably means some service of yours is not up and running. Check that the status of all services is green, or in the logs try to identify which client is not connecting.

So this error was seen on both crafting and aihub-sandbox. `file-service` is showing down via `ppy status file-service` even though its logs are populating and on the processes, it's showing it's up here (https://instabase.sandboxes.site/sandboxes/sayanbhattacharjee1?cw=dev)
Let me take a look if I can isolate the error

Seems this issue is affecting multiple environments (<#CCY413CSU|> channel post (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CCY413CSU/p1739212994324749?thread_ts=1739210358.205999&cid=CCY413CSU))
cc @Yash Botadra

Following on <#CCY413CSU|> channel
